{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LHG39dF8b3fGTsmxFoUn5Y","type":"tool_result","content":"   160→  // English — recipe-book chapter/category labels\n   161→  \"vegetables\", \"seafood\", \"fish\", \"soups\", \"salads\", \"desserts\",\n   162→  \"appetizers\", \"breads\", \"breakfast\", \"pasta\", \"grains\",\n   163→  \"main courses\", \"side dishes\", \"preserves\", \"baked goods\",\n   164→  \"fish & seafood\", \"soups & broths\", \"desserts & baked goods\",\n   165→  \"meats\", \"poultry\", \"game\",\n   166→]);\n   167→\n   168→function isSectionLabel(text: string): boolean {\n   169→  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n   170→  if (SECTION_LABELS.has(normalized)) return true;\n   171→  // OCR variant: leading \"l\" may be OCR-corrupted \"I\" (e.g. \"lngredients\" → \"ingredients\")\n   172→  const ocrNormalized = normalized.replace(/^l/, \"i\");\n   173→  if (ocrNormalized !== normalized && SECTION_LABELS.has(ocrNormalized)) return true;\n   174→  return false;\n   175→}\n   176→\n   177→/**\n   178→ * Recipe-internal section labels that should ALWAYS block multi-line joins,\n   179→ * even when the combined word count is ≥ 3.\n   180→ * Category labels (\"zupy\", \"placki\", etc.) are NOT in this set — they can\n   181→ * legitimately start a multi-word recipe title like \"Zupy Zimowe Warzywne\".\n   182→ */\n   183→const ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS = new Set([\n   184→  \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"preparation\",\n   185→  \"steps\", \"notes\", \"tip\", \"tips\", \"variations\", \"variation\",\n   186→  \"garnish\", \"topping\", \"toppings\", \"frosting\", \"filling\",\n   187→  \"serving suggestion\", \"serving suggestions\", \"serving\",\n   188→  \"glaze\", \"instrukcje\", \"uwagi\", \"notatki\", \"podawanie\", \"przechowywanie\",\n   189→  \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"sposob wykonania\",\n   190→  \"wykonanie\", \"wskazowki\", \"podpowiedz\", \"warianty\",\n   191→  \"sos\", \"nadzienie\", \"polewa\", \"lukier\", \"ciasto\",\n   192→]);\n   193→\n   194→function isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(text: string): boolean {\n   195→  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n   196→  return ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS.has(normalized);\n   197→}\n   198→\n   199→function isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n   200→  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n   201→  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n   202→}\n   203→\n   204→function looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n   205→  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n   206→}\n   207→\n   208→function isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n   209→  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015NrLtSxACtsf1SWsF7BGqz","session_id":"7a79a908-8d4c-4852-8920-c5c4df3c5fbb","uuid":"b7adf829-a9d9-46ee-9344-7f2414052682"}
